22
00:01:38,932 --> 00:01:44,021
♪

23
00:01:44,021 --> 00:01:46,565
(snoring)

24
00:01:46,565 --> 00:02:04,458
♪

25
00:02:04,458 --> 00:02:07,419
Huh, you?

26
00:02:07,419 --> 00:02:09,087
But, how the hell did‐‐

27
00:02:09,087 --> 00:02:10,464
(yelps)

28
00:02:10,464 --> 00:02:12,466
♪

29
00:02:12,466 --> 00:02:13,508
You bastard, I'll‐‐

30
00:02:13,508 --> 00:02:17,220
(grunting)

31
00:02:18,680 --> 00:02:20,557
(guttural moans)

32
00:02:20,557 --> 00:02:30,442
♪

33
00:02:30,442 --> 00:02:32,944
(typewriter keys clicking)

34
00:02:34,780 --> 00:02:43,955
♪

35
00:02:43,955 --> 00:02:46,124
What, did I just hear you right?

36
00:02:46,124 --> 00:02:47,209
In Hawaii?

37
00:02:47,209 --> 00:02:50,128
You want me to deliver
a presentation on Lupin's

38
00:02:50,128 --> 00:02:51,338
whole career?

39
00:02:51,338 --> 00:02:55,801
Precisely, the request
comes straight from the top.

40
00:02:55,801 --> 00:02:57,094
There's to be an international

41
00:02:57,094 --> 00:02:58,845
law enforcement
conference there.

42
00:02:58,845 --> 00:03:00,430
You'll be a special
guest speaker.

43
00:03:00,430 --> 00:03:03,016
Hmm, a special guest, huh?

44
00:03:03,016 --> 00:03:07,396
That means that I'm sort
of a, you know, a VIP!

45
00:03:07,396 --> 00:03:10,941
Mm‐hmm, that's right.

46
00:03:10,941 --> 00:03:13,151
Thanks, sir, but I
just can't do it!

47
00:03:13,151 --> 00:03:16,071
With all due respect,
fancy conferences

48
00:03:16,071 --> 00:03:18,907
and exotic locations
are all fine and well, sir,

49
00:03:18,907 --> 00:03:21,702
but my first obligation is‐‐

50
00:03:21,702 --> 00:03:24,329
You damned fool,
this is an order!

51
00:03:24,329 --> 00:03:25,247
It is?

52
00:03:25,247 --> 00:03:27,332
Besides, this is
an incredible honor.

53
00:03:27,332 --> 00:03:30,669
You are being recognized
as an expert internationally

54
00:03:30,669 --> 00:03:32,921
on the foremost
criminal of our times.

55
00:03:32,921 --> 00:03:34,840
Inspector, this should
be the proudest moment

56
00:03:34,840 --> 00:03:36,508
of your career.

57
00:03:36,508 --> 00:03:39,136
It's my proudest moment, huh?

58
00:03:39,136 --> 00:03:41,346
Can I keep my frequent
flyer miles, sir?

59
00:03:41,346 --> 00:03:43,765
I'd like to get to work
on the big speech,

60
00:03:43,765 --> 00:03:45,142
if it's all right with you.

61
00:03:45,142 --> 00:03:46,768
Request permission
to leave, sir.

62
00:03:46,768 --> 00:03:49,521
You can do that
on the plane, Inspector.

63
00:03:49,521 --> 00:03:52,607
There's your passport;
your flight leaves in two hours.

64
00:03:52,607 --> 00:03:53,942
Well, get moving!

65
00:03:53,942 --> 00:03:56,403
(jet roaring)

66
00:04:00,699 --> 00:04:04,703
♪

67
00:04:04,703 --> 00:04:05,787
Well, there he goes.

68
00:04:05,787 --> 00:04:07,747
He's definitely
on board, I checked.

69
00:04:07,747 --> 00:04:09,082
That's good news, Jigen.

70
00:04:09,082 --> 00:04:10,417
That means things will be nice

71
00:04:10,417 --> 00:04:12,878
and quiet for
a little while, anyway.

72
00:04:12,878 --> 00:04:16,548
How about we toast to it?

73
00:04:16,548 --> 00:04:18,216
That's great,
I'm looking forward

74
00:04:18,216 --> 00:04:19,259
to just kicking‐‐

75
00:04:19,259 --> 00:04:20,844
(grunting)

76
00:04:20,844 --> 00:04:26,349
♪

77
00:04:26,349 --> 00:04:28,810
(engine revs)

78
00:04:31,396 --> 00:04:33,273
(tires screeching)

79
00:04:33,273 --> 00:04:35,984
(door opens)

80
00:04:35,984 --> 00:04:41,406
♪

81
00:04:41,406 --> 00:04:42,908
Hey there, Beauty.

82
00:04:42,908 --> 00:04:45,660
Guten tag, Jigen,
you haven't changed a bit.

83
00:04:45,660 --> 00:04:47,621
Yeah, so what
the hell do you want?

84
00:04:47,621 --> 00:04:49,664
Not here to kill you,
if that's what you're

85
00:04:49,664 --> 00:04:50,832
worried about.

86
00:04:50,832 --> 00:04:54,377
I'm here for Sideburn Boy.

87
00:04:54,377 --> 00:04:58,423
Lupin, INTERPOL's decided
to put a bounty on your head.

88
00:04:58,423 --> 00:04:59,382
You're kiddin' me!

89
00:04:59,382 --> 00:05:00,675
That doesn't sound like them.

90
00:05:00,675 --> 00:05:03,428
Too bad; you're getting
to be an embarrassment.

91
00:05:03,428 --> 00:05:06,264
So, they came to me
to take care of it.

92
00:05:06,264 --> 00:05:08,183
You are the best, Beauty.

93
00:05:08,183 --> 00:05:10,435
Hey, wait, here's
a crazy thought:

94
00:05:10,435 --> 00:05:12,604
Why don't you tell 'em
I couldn't be found?

95
00:05:12,604 --> 00:05:16,149
If you can't find a guy,
then you can't kill him.

96
00:05:16,149 --> 00:05:19,861
I will give you until tomorrow
to get your affairs in order,

97
00:05:19,861 --> 00:05:23,865
make one last pathetic play
for Fujiko, stuff like that.

98
00:05:23,865 --> 00:05:25,283
Nothing personal, you know?

99
00:05:25,283 --> 00:05:27,869
It's all just business, bye‐bye.

100
00:05:27,869 --> 00:05:30,288
♪

101
00:05:30,288 --> 00:05:32,791
(tires screech)

102
00:05:42,717 --> 00:05:45,178
♪

103
00:05:45,178 --> 00:05:46,471
Well, that's bad news.

104
00:05:46,471 --> 00:05:48,557
New York's demon
detective is back.

105
00:05:48,557 --> 00:05:50,976
I don't know how the hell
the guy ever earned a promotion.

106
00:05:50,976 --> 00:05:53,645
I tell ya, INTERPOL
sure is going downhill.

107
00:05:53,645 --> 00:05:58,149
He's just overcompensating
for that nickname, that's all.

108
00:05:58,149 --> 00:06:00,151
Come on, Lupin,
you said it yourself,

109
00:06:00,151 --> 00:06:01,236
Beauty's the best.

110
00:06:01,236 --> 00:06:03,029
And that big‐ass gun he carries,

111
00:06:03,029 --> 00:06:05,323
it's a . 44 caliber
Colt‐8 Python.

112
00:06:05,323 --> 00:06:07,701
That's the most powerful
handgun in the world.

113
00:06:07,701 --> 00:06:09,703
Lupin, come on,
let's just get outta here

114
00:06:09,703 --> 00:06:11,830
for a little while, you know,
to somewhere like Tahiti

115
00:06:11,830 --> 00:06:12,747
or something.

116
00:06:12,747 --> 00:06:15,000
Hey, Fujiko,
I'm not Gauguin, you know?

117
00:06:15,000 --> 00:06:16,376
I'm a thief.

118
00:06:16,376 --> 00:06:17,752
You've got the wrong guy.

119
00:06:17,752 --> 00:06:20,171
While I'm not an expert
in firearms, I can tell you

120
00:06:20,171 --> 00:06:23,258
that the man carries the aura
of a dangerous killer.

121
00:06:23,258 --> 00:06:25,343
Lupin, listen to me,
it would be suicide

122
00:06:25,343 --> 00:06:26,678
to let pride get in your way.

123
00:06:26,678 --> 00:06:30,473
This maniac is
a killer with a badge.

124
00:06:30,473 --> 00:06:33,560
♪

125
00:06:33,560 --> 00:06:37,397
(singing in foreign language)

126
00:06:37,397 --> 00:06:40,692
♪

127
00:06:40,692 --> 00:06:43,153
(laughing)

128
00:06:43,153 --> 00:06:45,780
Aloha!

129
00:06:45,780 --> 00:06:47,115
Well, thanks!

130
00:06:47,115 --> 00:06:49,618
The same to you, toots!

131
00:06:49,618 --> 00:06:51,369
Mr. Zenigata!

132
00:06:51,369 --> 00:06:52,621
Aren't you sweet?

133
00:06:52,621 --> 00:06:55,040
(kissing)

134
00:06:55,040 --> 00:06:58,335
Yuck!

135
00:06:58,335 --> 00:07:00,629
So, I am a VIP!

136
00:07:00,629 --> 00:07:02,255
There's only one thing missing,

137
00:07:02,255 --> 00:07:05,216
and that thing is rubbing
my newfound celebrity

138
00:07:05,216 --> 00:07:09,387
in the smirking chimp‐like
face of Lupin the Third!

139
00:07:09,387 --> 00:07:12,223
Look, man, you gotta get
your ego out of this.

140
00:07:12,223 --> 00:07:13,725
Beauty's just way
out of your league

141
00:07:13,725 --> 00:07:15,894
and there's zero shame
in admitting it.

142
00:07:15,894 --> 00:07:18,229
Jigen, you're making
too much of this.

143
00:07:18,229 --> 00:07:19,731
Oh, yeah, you think so, huh?

144
00:07:19,731 --> 00:07:23,360
Listen, it was
just six years ago.

145
00:07:23,360 --> 00:07:25,403
♪

146
00:07:25,403 --> 00:07:27,447
I was at the peak
of my powers, right?

147
00:07:27,447 --> 00:07:29,115
Almost as cocky as you.

148
00:07:29,115 --> 00:07:36,790
♪

149
00:07:36,790 --> 00:07:38,667
(gunfire)

150
00:07:38,667 --> 00:07:43,463
♪

151
00:07:43,463 --> 00:07:45,423
(tires screeching)

152
00:07:45,423 --> 00:07:47,717
♪

153
00:07:47,717 --> 00:07:49,135
Huh?

154
00:07:49,135 --> 00:07:51,346
♪

155
00:07:51,346 --> 00:07:53,223
(gunshot)

156
00:07:53,223 --> 00:07:55,684
(screeching)

157
00:07:58,687 --> 00:07:59,688
(gunshot)

158
00:07:59,688 --> 00:08:01,648
(explosion)

159
00:08:01,648 --> 00:08:04,150
(screeching, crash)

160
00:08:07,779 --> 00:08:10,323
(panting)

161
00:08:10,323 --> 00:08:12,117
♪

162
00:08:12,117 --> 00:08:14,577
I ran, and I'm not
the least bit ashamed

163
00:08:14,577 --> 00:08:16,037
to say it.

164
00:08:16,037 --> 00:08:18,289
Think of it as
a tactical retreat, Lupin.

165
00:08:18,289 --> 00:08:21,251
This is just a battle,
not the entire war.

166
00:08:21,251 --> 00:08:22,836
Don't patronize me!

167
00:08:22,836 --> 00:08:26,381
Look, you guys, if I don't
step up to this challenge,

168
00:08:26,381 --> 00:08:29,718
then I'd better just quit.

169
00:08:29,718 --> 00:08:31,761
You're a fool, damn you!

170
00:08:31,761 --> 00:08:33,304
Dickhead!

171
00:08:33,304 --> 00:08:36,057
He's a much better shot
than you, with a better gun!

172
00:08:36,057 --> 00:08:39,102
You duel with him
and you're dead!

173
00:08:39,102 --> 00:08:39,978
Old‐fashioned?

174
00:08:39,978 --> 00:08:41,938
Yes, of course,
guilty as charged!

175
00:08:41,938 --> 00:08:44,607
It's all about the law;
it's not about revenge.

176
00:08:44,607 --> 00:08:46,818
Sure, part of me would love
to take on Lupin with

177
00:08:46,818 --> 00:08:49,529
my bare fists and give him
a good thrashing or even worse!

178
00:08:49,529 --> 00:08:53,158
But nobody hired me to be
judge, jury, and executioner.

179
00:08:53,158 --> 00:08:55,660
It was the great
Charlie Chaplin, I think,

180
00:08:55,660 --> 00:08:57,287
who said‐‐yeah,
this is it,

181
00:08:57,287 --> 00:08:59,998
"Kill one murderer and you're
nothing but a criminal,

182
00:08:59,998 --> 00:09:02,959
but kill a million criminals
and you're a heroic,

183
00:09:02,959 --> 00:09:04,419
endearing little tramp."

184
00:09:04,419 --> 00:09:07,756
That wasn't exactly it
but it's still true today!

185
00:09:07,756 --> 00:09:10,091
(applause)

186
00:09:12,761 --> 00:09:14,137
Thank you, thank you!

187
00:09:14,137 --> 00:09:17,932
Really, take it easy, now.

188
00:09:17,932 --> 00:09:19,642
His gun is better than mine?

189
00:09:19,642 --> 00:09:21,728
What do you mean by that?

190
00:09:21,728 --> 00:09:23,980
Look, this is your Walther‐‐
it's a great gun

191
00:09:23,980 --> 00:09:26,608
and the double‐action it has
makes the P38 the best

192
00:09:26,608 --> 00:09:28,526
automatic pistol
in the world.

193
00:09:28,526 --> 00:09:31,112
The ballistic course of
the Parabellum is real stable.

194
00:09:31,112 --> 00:09:33,198
It's a classic,
no doubt about it.

195
00:09:33,198 --> 00:09:34,532
Then we agree?

196
00:09:34,532 --> 00:09:38,078
Except that your Walther
doesn't shoot mags.

197
00:09:38,078 --> 00:09:41,289
♪

198
00:09:41,289 --> 00:09:44,417
For that, you gotta have a . 357.

199
00:09:44,417 --> 00:09:47,962
Like this, the good old
Smith & Wesson . 357 Magnum:

200
00:09:47,962 --> 00:09:50,465
a classic with cojones.

201
00:09:50,465 --> 00:09:53,218
(gun clicking)

202
00:09:53,218 --> 00:09:55,970
(gunshot)

203
00:09:55,970 --> 00:09:58,431
(gunfire)

204
00:10:03,228 --> 00:10:06,815
Jigen, I know that a . 357's
got the destructive edge,

205
00:10:06,815 --> 00:10:08,566
but it just isn't as accurate.

206
00:10:08,566 --> 00:10:12,028
Speaking of accuracy,
I noticed something about

207
00:10:12,028 --> 00:10:14,656
that gun that Beauty was
waving around yesterday.

208
00:10:14,656 --> 00:10:17,200
It's got a Venturi built on it
and that's used for cooling

209
00:10:17,200 --> 00:10:20,120
the barrel so that the heat
won't affect your aim.

210
00:10:20,120 --> 00:10:21,579
It's state‐of‐the‐art.

211
00:10:21,579 --> 00:10:24,332
Your Walther P38
was originally manufactured

212
00:10:24,332 --> 00:10:26,209
all the way back in the 1930s.

213
00:10:26,209 --> 00:10:29,087
All I'm saying is Beauty's
got a . 44 Colt‐8 Python

214
00:10:29,087 --> 00:10:30,588
that was made only
a few years ago,

215
00:10:30,588 --> 00:10:34,217
and that's the difference‐‐
you do the math, Lupin.

216
00:10:34,217 --> 00:10:36,594
This is Jigen's area
of mastery, Lupin.

217
00:10:36,594 --> 00:10:39,430
To choose to ignore his advice
is to choose the path

218
00:10:39,430 --> 00:10:40,765
of fatal folly.

219
00:10:40,765 --> 00:10:44,352
♪

220
00:10:44,352 --> 00:10:46,437
What, but that's insane?

221
00:10:46,437 --> 00:10:48,148
Kill Lupin?

222
00:10:48,148 --> 00:10:50,108
Yes, I swear that it's true.

223
00:10:50,108 --> 00:10:53,111
So, they set me up
with this damn conference

224
00:10:53,111 --> 00:10:55,029
while they dispatch Beauty to‐‐

225
00:10:55,029 --> 00:10:57,782
Hmm, so, that's their game!

226
00:10:57,782 --> 00:11:00,368
You've gotta do something,
Inspector, please?

227
00:11:00,368 --> 00:11:04,455
All right, keep your shirt on!

228
00:11:04,455 --> 00:11:06,291
I'll take care of this!

229
00:11:09,252 --> 00:11:10,879
Sorry, guys, had to do it.

230
00:11:10,879 --> 00:11:12,088
Anyway, one way or the other,

231
00:11:12,088 --> 00:11:15,341
it'll all be over
by the time you find me.

232
00:11:15,341 --> 00:11:17,969
For me, this is just
about being alive.

233
00:11:17,969 --> 00:11:21,556
A guy can't run every time
some guy wants to do him in.

234
00:11:21,556 --> 00:11:23,892
You just gotta face it.

235
00:11:23,892 --> 00:11:26,227
(gun clacking)

236
00:11:26,227 --> 00:11:30,940
♪

237
00:11:30,940 --> 00:11:32,942
And find out whatcha got.

238
00:11:32,942 --> 00:11:39,824
♪

239
00:11:39,824 --> 00:11:41,910
(engine revving)

240
00:11:41,910 --> 00:11:44,370
♪

241
00:11:44,370 --> 00:11:46,080
(tires squealing)

242
00:11:46,080 --> 00:11:49,292
(yelping)

243
00:11:49,292 --> 00:11:51,920
(engine revving)

244
00:11:57,342 --> 00:11:59,510
(chuckles)

245
00:11:59,510 --> 00:12:02,889
(yelps)

246
00:12:02,889 --> 00:12:05,350
(screeching)

247
00:12:12,523 --> 00:12:15,235
(gunshot)

248
00:12:15,235 --> 00:12:18,446
(screeching)

249
00:12:18,446 --> 00:12:20,823
(explosion)

250
00:12:20,823 --> 00:12:22,784
Huh?

251
00:12:22,784 --> 00:12:25,745
Agh, dammit, Lupin
took off to find Beauty!

252
00:12:25,745 --> 00:12:31,459
♪

253
00:12:31,459 --> 00:12:34,254
♪ Lupin the Third ♪

254
00:12:38,258 --> 00:12:41,344
♪ Lupin the Third ♪

255
00:12:41,344 --> 00:12:43,805
(fire crackling)

256
00:12:59,404 --> 00:13:01,864
(engine revving)

257
00:13:06,452 --> 00:13:08,663
(explosion)

258
00:13:08,663 --> 00:13:13,084
♪

259
00:13:13,084 --> 00:13:15,545
(grunting)

260
00:13:17,130 --> 00:13:18,256
(chuckling)

261
00:13:18,256 --> 00:13:20,967
Not bad, but don't
gloat just yet, Beauty.

262
00:13:20,967 --> 00:13:22,927
I'm not handing myself
to you on a platter,

263
00:13:22,927 --> 00:13:26,347
You've gotta take me.

264
00:13:26,347 --> 00:13:30,059
Make my day.

265
00:13:30,059 --> 00:13:31,519
(grunts)

266
00:13:31,519 --> 00:13:33,771
(panting)

267
00:13:33,771 --> 00:13:46,075
♪

268
00:13:46,075 --> 00:13:47,618
Heh.

269
00:13:47,618 --> 00:13:50,038
Better an execution
than a shootout, Lupin.

270
00:13:50,038 --> 00:13:54,083
Believe me, a lot
less humiliating.

271
00:13:54,083 --> 00:13:56,169
(gunshots)

272
00:14:10,933 --> 00:14:13,019
Idiot.

273
00:14:20,985 --> 00:14:22,445
Huh?

274
00:14:22,445 --> 00:14:27,950
♪

275
00:14:27,950 --> 00:14:29,744
(gunshots)

276
00:14:29,744 --> 00:14:32,747
♪

277
00:14:32,747 --> 00:14:34,540
What the hell's going on?

278
00:14:34,540 --> 00:14:36,000
Damn!

279
00:14:36,000 --> 00:14:41,631
♪

280
00:14:41,631 --> 00:14:45,301
(guns cock)

281
00:14:52,433 --> 00:14:54,227
(gunshot)

282
00:14:54,227 --> 00:15:07,949
♪

283
00:15:07,949 --> 00:15:11,619
Playtime is over,
see you in hell.

284
00:15:11,619 --> 00:15:14,372
Not so fast, Beauty, hold it!

285
00:15:14,372 --> 00:15:18,626
Hey, I said wait!

286
00:15:18,626 --> 00:15:22,046
Whoa!

287
00:15:22,046 --> 00:15:22,880
(gasps)

288
00:15:22,880 --> 00:15:25,299
Lupin, talk to me,
are you all right?

289
00:15:25,299 --> 00:15:28,136
(grunting)

290
00:15:28,136 --> 00:15:29,679
Come on, were you hurt?

291
00:15:29,679 --> 00:15:31,013
Talk to me.

292
00:15:31,013 --> 00:15:33,182
The sun, it's setting.

293
00:15:33,182 --> 00:15:39,564
Seems kinda early for it,
but I guess it's just my time.

294
00:15:39,564 --> 00:15:43,401
No, it isn't, Lupin,
it's not your time yet!

295
00:15:43,401 --> 00:15:45,444
(chuckles)

296
00:15:45,444 --> 00:15:51,534
♪

297
00:15:51,534 --> 00:15:54,829
Proud of yourself, are ya, huh?

298
00:15:54,829 --> 00:15:57,456
I oughta‐‐Beauty, you bastard!

299
00:15:57,456 --> 00:15:59,750
He's a sadist too, killing's
not good enough for him,

300
00:15:59,750 --> 00:16:01,919
I guess the guy has to use
hollow‐point bullets just

301
00:16:01,919 --> 00:16:03,796
to make his victims suffer.

302
00:16:03,796 --> 00:16:05,715
Well, is that the truth, Beauty?

303
00:16:05,715 --> 00:16:07,258
You're actually using dum‐dums?

304
00:16:07,258 --> 00:16:08,426
Those things are‐‐

305
00:16:08,426 --> 00:16:09,427
Illegal, they have
been ever since

306
00:16:09,427 --> 00:16:12,346
the Treaty
of Versailles of 1929.

307
00:16:12,346 --> 00:16:13,639
I don't know a whole
lot of history,

308
00:16:13,639 --> 00:16:15,433
but if it affects me,
I remember it.

309
00:16:15,433 --> 00:16:16,684
Treaty of Versailles?

310
00:16:16,684 --> 00:16:18,102
It's all coming back.

311
00:16:18,102 --> 00:16:20,771
The police are forbidden
from using those!

312
00:16:20,771 --> 00:16:21,939
Hey!

313
00:16:21,939 --> 00:16:23,399
And your point, Inspector?

314
00:16:23,399 --> 00:16:25,401
If the order is for
extreme prejudice,

315
00:16:25,401 --> 00:16:26,986
it doesn't make any difference

316
00:16:26,986 --> 00:16:29,530
if the guy suffers
a little but more.

317
00:16:29,530 --> 00:16:32,825
I mean, he is
the enemy, isn't he?

318
00:16:32,825 --> 00:16:35,286
(thunder)

319
00:16:35,286 --> 00:16:37,747
(rainfall)

320
00:16:41,000 --> 00:16:43,502
(continuous thunder)

321
00:16:56,974 --> 00:16:59,810
Oh, just look at me,
I'm soaking!

322
00:16:59,810 --> 00:17:01,354
What weather!

323
00:17:01,354 --> 00:17:03,064
Oh, man, it was
so freakin' cold,

324
00:17:03,064 --> 00:17:04,649
I was freezin' my ass off!

325
00:17:04,649 --> 00:17:07,652
I know, the weather was biblical
in its ferocity and sense

326
00:17:07,652 --> 00:17:09,028
of dark foreboding.

327
00:17:09,028 --> 00:17:10,947
Listen to you guys:
bitch, bitch, bitch!

328
00:17:10,947 --> 00:17:13,324
Look at me, what
the hell's going on?

329
00:17:13,324 --> 00:17:16,410
I'm fine, so what's
with the funeral, well?

330
00:17:16,410 --> 00:17:18,996
Hey, Lupin, you have no clue
how close you came to needing

331
00:17:18,996 --> 00:17:21,832
that funeral.

332
00:17:21,832 --> 00:17:24,460
Friggin' bastard was packin'
hollow‐points in that gun

333
00:17:24,460 --> 00:17:26,337
of his, you realize that?

334
00:17:26,337 --> 00:17:28,089
There wouldn't have been
enough of you left to pour

335
00:17:28,089 --> 00:17:31,300
into that damn body cast
if just one of 'em hit ya.

336
00:17:31,300 --> 00:17:39,433
♪

337
00:17:39,433 --> 00:17:42,144
(gunfire)

338
00:17:42,144 --> 00:17:44,313
(rumbling)

339
00:17:44,313 --> 00:17:46,899
I dropped an adhesive
load on that rock.

340
00:17:48,943 --> 00:17:55,324
♪

341
00:17:55,324 --> 00:17:57,159
Just in time.

342
00:17:57,159 --> 00:17:59,870
I can't believe it,
what kind of a sadist is he?

343
00:17:59,870 --> 00:18:02,206
That bastard's really
gonna pay for this!

344
00:18:02,206 --> 00:18:05,793
(grunting)

345
00:18:05,793 --> 00:18:08,838
Hey, you just stay here
and get some rest.

346
00:18:08,838 --> 00:18:12,717
(whimpering)

347
00:18:12,717 --> 00:18:15,177
(jet roaring)

348
00:18:20,850 --> 00:18:24,020
Incoming message for
Inspector Beauty of INTERPOL.

349
00:18:24,020 --> 00:18:26,897
Inspector Beauty of INTERPOL,
please pick up your headset

350
00:18:26,897 --> 00:18:29,900
for a message.

351
00:18:29,900 --> 00:18:32,028
Listen to you guys:
bitch, bitch, bitch!

352
00:18:32,028 --> 00:18:35,489
Look at me, I can't believe it!

353
00:18:35,489 --> 00:18:36,907
What kind of a sadist is he?

354
00:18:36,907 --> 00:18:39,243
That bastard's really
gonna pay for this!

355
00:18:39,243 --> 00:18:45,207
♪

356
00:18:45,207 --> 00:18:46,959
(growls)

357
00:18:46,959 --> 00:18:51,881
♪

358
00:18:51,881 --> 00:18:55,760
Come in!

359
00:18:55,760 --> 00:18:58,054
Where's Lupin?

360
00:18:58,054 --> 00:19:00,306
Is this a trick question?

361
00:19:00,306 --> 00:19:04,935
♪

362
00:19:04,935 --> 00:19:07,938
What, well, let's just say
the thing's not a hoax

363
00:19:07,938 --> 00:19:10,566
and I don't have any orders
to help you and I wouldn't

364
00:19:10,566 --> 00:19:15,404
want to even if I did, and now,
I've got goodies to eat!

365
00:19:15,404 --> 00:19:17,406
I'll still find him.

366
00:19:17,406 --> 00:19:18,991
(gunfire)

367
00:19:18,991 --> 00:19:21,243
Whoa!

368
00:19:21,243 --> 00:19:22,328
So, you're the hunted?

369
00:19:22,328 --> 00:19:24,413
How's that make ya feel, friend?

370
00:19:24,413 --> 00:19:29,126
♪

371
00:19:29,126 --> 00:19:32,755
(humming)

372
00:19:32,755 --> 00:19:33,964
Why all the thermometers?

373
00:19:33,964 --> 00:19:35,132
What are you doing?

374
00:19:35,132 --> 00:19:37,009
I'm fighting fire with fire;

375
00:19:37,009 --> 00:19:38,511
if he wants to use dum‐dums,

376
00:19:38,511 --> 00:19:40,638
then I'll just have
to raise him.

377
00:19:40,638 --> 00:19:43,224
My own invention:
mercury bullets!

378
00:19:43,224 --> 00:19:45,643
Lupin, I don't think
you're taking this seriously!

379
00:19:45,643 --> 00:19:47,395
There's no time
for joking around.

380
00:19:47,395 --> 00:19:49,605
I promise I'm not joking around,

381
00:19:49,605 --> 00:19:50,940
so come on, will ya?

382
00:19:50,940 --> 00:19:52,900
Give me a hand
breaking these things.

383
00:19:52,900 --> 00:19:54,151
Gently, now.

384
00:19:54,151 --> 00:20:00,157
♪

385
00:20:00,157 --> 00:20:02,326
Watch out, Beauty,
I'm comin' for ya!

386
00:20:02,326 --> 00:20:05,287
I've never heard
of a mercury bullet.

387
00:20:05,287 --> 00:20:08,708
I lied before, it's really
not my invention at all.

388
00:20:08,708 --> 00:20:10,918
Believe it not, it comes
straight out of a book

389
00:20:10,918 --> 00:20:12,586
by Ernest Hemingway.

390
00:20:12,586 --> 00:20:14,422
Supposedly, just a single bullet

391
00:20:14,422 --> 00:20:16,465
can bring down
a charging bull elephant,

392
00:20:16,465 --> 00:20:18,008
that's how lethal this stuff is.

393
00:20:18,008 --> 00:20:19,635
See, as soon as
it hits the target,

394
00:20:19,635 --> 00:20:23,264
the impact releases the mercury
straight into the bloodstream.

395
00:20:23,264 --> 00:20:29,478
♪

396
00:20:29,478 --> 00:20:31,355
That's it, nothing he
can do about it,

397
00:20:31,355 --> 00:20:32,982
taken totally by surprise.

398
00:20:32,982 --> 00:20:35,860
Beauty won't even have the
time to know he's surprised.

399
00:20:35,860 --> 00:20:37,695
By the way, Lupin,
what do you know

400
00:20:37,695 --> 00:20:40,698
about mixing
explosives with mercury?

401
00:20:40,698 --> 00:20:41,991
Nothing, I guess, why?

402
00:20:41,991 --> 00:20:44,452
Lupin, it's dangerous!

403
00:20:44,452 --> 00:20:46,245
Don't worry yourself, Fujicakes!

404
00:20:46,245 --> 00:20:48,289
I'm nobody's smithereen.

405
00:20:48,289 --> 00:20:50,875
♪

406
00:20:50,875 --> 00:20:52,835
Jeez, have a little
faith, will ya?

407
00:20:52,835 --> 00:20:58,382
♪

408
00:20:58,382 --> 00:20:59,842
(wind whooshing)

409
00:20:59,842 --> 00:21:01,469
I sure hope it
didn't ruin your day

410
00:21:01,469 --> 00:21:04,305
to find out that
Lupin's still alive.

411
00:21:04,305 --> 00:21:06,849
Lovely location
for our showdown.

412
00:21:06,849 --> 00:21:08,976
Point is Dream Island's
a landfill, which make it

413
00:21:08,976 --> 00:21:11,353
kind of a perfect place
for burying trash.

414
00:21:11,353 --> 00:21:14,857
Big talk from a guy whose
specialty is turning tail!

415
00:21:14,857 --> 00:21:16,233
(laughing)

416
00:21:16,233 --> 00:21:17,860
You know, Beauty,
ever since that night,

417
00:21:17,860 --> 00:21:20,321
I thought about facing off with
you and yet it only occurred

418
00:21:20,321 --> 00:21:22,615
to me just yesterday
what your Achilles heel

419
00:21:22,615 --> 00:21:24,992
actually is, and, you know,
it's kinda funny when you

420
00:21:24,992 --> 00:21:26,327
think about it.

421
00:21:26,327 --> 00:21:27,495
Huh?

422
00:21:27,495 --> 00:21:29,830
That big piece you carry
is real scary, but the fact is

423
00:21:29,830 --> 00:21:33,083
you need both hands just
to shoot the damn thing.

424
00:21:33,083 --> 00:21:36,462
Wanna see just how big
a liability it is?

425
00:21:36,462 --> 00:21:38,214
Anytime, pretty boy.

426
00:21:41,425 --> 00:21:44,261
(gunshot)

427
00:21:44,261 --> 00:21:45,930
How in the hell did you do that?

428
00:21:45,930 --> 00:21:47,139
It's impossible!

429
00:21:47,139 --> 00:21:49,058
Damn.

430
00:21:49,058 --> 00:21:51,101
Jigen, I'm the best there is.

431
00:21:51,101 --> 00:21:52,978
Why the hell do you think
INTERPOL picked me

432
00:21:52,978 --> 00:21:54,814
for this assignment?

433
00:21:54,814 --> 00:21:57,107
And on top of that,
they also promised me

434
00:21:57,107 --> 00:21:59,527
a pretty nifty Christmas bonus.

435
00:21:59,527 --> 00:22:01,195
Man, so this is how I end up.

436
00:22:01,195 --> 00:22:03,239
Shame you can't
run away this time.

437
00:22:03,239 --> 00:22:05,449
(cocks gun)

438
00:22:05,449 --> 00:22:07,743
(screeching)

439
00:22:07,743 --> 00:22:08,994
(engine revs)

440
00:22:08,994 --> 00:22:11,956
♪

441
00:22:11,956 --> 00:22:13,958
Listen‐‐

442
00:22:13,958 --> 00:22:14,959
What the hell?

443
00:22:14,959 --> 00:22:16,126
Look, there's a
pretty good chance

444
00:22:16,126 --> 00:22:17,878
we're gonna die here,
but I say we give it

445
00:22:17,878 --> 00:22:18,838
a shot, okay?

446
00:22:18,838 --> 00:22:20,673
So, here's a little
present I made for ya;

447
00:22:20,673 --> 00:22:23,592
it's a one‐of‐a‐kind bullet
with a mercury payload.

448
00:22:23,592 --> 00:22:25,678
Use my shoulder.

449
00:22:25,678 --> 00:22:28,305
(cocks gun)

450
00:22:28,305 --> 00:22:29,974
Here goes nothing.

451
00:22:29,974 --> 00:22:32,017
♪

452
00:22:32,017 --> 00:22:33,644
Now, Jigen, do it!

453
00:22:33,644 --> 00:22:34,770
(gunshot)

454
00:22:34,770 --> 00:22:37,273
(agonized screaming)

455
00:22:45,614 --> 00:22:47,992
Was it, uh, supposed
to work like that?

456
00:22:47,992 --> 00:22:49,785
I'm not a chemist
or anything, you know,

457
00:22:49,785 --> 00:22:53,247
but I think I mighta added
a little too much explosive.

458
00:22:53,247 --> 00:22:54,623
Probably shouldn't do that kind

459
00:22:54,623 --> 00:22:56,458
of thing when you're
in a bad mood.

460
00:22:56,458 --> 00:22:57,960
(yelping)

461
00:22:57,960 --> 00:22:59,670
Wait, she needs mouth to mouth?

462
00:22:59,670 --> 00:23:00,629
Chest compression?

463
00:23:00,629 --> 00:23:02,006
Hey, that's my job!

464
00:23:02,006 --> 00:23:03,424
D'oh!

465
00:23:03,424 --> 00:23:06,927
♪

466
00:23:11,348 --> 00:23:13,142
♪ Lupin the Third ♪

467
00:23:13,142 --> 00:23:14,476
Confused‐‐join the club!

468
00:23:14,476 --> 00:23:16,186
It's enough to make you
pull your face off.

469
00:23:16,186 --> 00:23:17,938
Giant monkeys,
human chess pieces,

470
00:23:17,938 --> 00:23:19,523
or are they actually
normal‐sized monkeys

471
00:23:19,523 --> 00:23:20,816
and we've all been
shrunk to the size

472
00:23:20,816 --> 00:23:22,234
of Lupin collectables?

473
00:23:22,234 --> 00:23:23,527
Either way, we're in a fix.

474
00:23:23,527 --> 00:23:25,821
Join us next time as we live
to regret out latest search

475
00:23:25,821 --> 00:23:28,657
for a mysterious treasure in
"Monkey King Business"!

476
00:23:28,657 --> 00:23:29,992
Catch ya later!

477
00:23:29,992 --> 00:24:39,520
♪

